uced by the asymmetric distribution of the\nmagnetic fields on the two sides of the filament may cause the observed rolling\nmotion. The rotating motion of the prominence threads observed by AIA is\nconsistent with the removal of the field line dips in Model 2 from the top down\nduring the eruption.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 29 Nov 2012 16:29:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-12"}
