{"id":"1211.7224","submitter":"Tommaso Tufarelli Dr","authors":"Cyril Vaneph, Tommaso Tufarelli, Marco G. Genoni","title":"Quantum estimation of a two-phase spin rotation","comments":"9 pages, 3 figures","journal-ref":"Quantum Measurements and Quantum Metrology 1, 12 (2013)","doi":"10.2478/qmetro-2013-0003","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We study the estimation of an infinitesimal rotation of a spin-j system,\ncharacterized by two unknown phases, and compare the estimation precision\nachievable with two different strategies. The first is a standard `joint\nestimation' strategy, in which a single probe state is used to estimate both\nparameters, while the second is a `sequential' strategy in which the two phases\nare estimated separately, each on half of the total number of system copies. In\nthe limit of small angles we show that, although the joint estimation approach\nyields in general a better performance, the two strategies possess the same\nscaling of the total phase sensitivity with respect to the spin number j,\nnamely $\\Delta\\Phi \\simeq 1/j$. Finally, we discuss a simple estimation\nstrategy based on spin squeezed states and spin measurements, and compare its\nperformance with the ultimate limits to the estimation precision that we have\nderived above.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 30 Nov 2012 12:03:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 2 Apr 2013 18:00:31 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 10 Sep 2013 11:47:18 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 3 Jun 2019 15:50:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-06-04"}
